uistics in Bamberg (February 27-29, 2008), and additional papers, which have been especially commissioned for this volume. Its main focus lies on providing further empirical evidence about languages that have various - lexical as well as grammatical - evidential expressions. The papers in this volume will offer a cross-linguistic perspective on this topic as they deal with a number of different language families and languages: Romance languages (French, Spanish, Italian), Germanic languages (Dutch, German, English, Icelandic), Baltic and Slavic languages, Greek, Basque, and Turkish.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aEvidentials (Linguistics). 0aTypology (Linguistics). 4aEuropa. 4aEvidentialität. 4aSprache. 4aSprachtypologie. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aEvidentiality.  aLanguage Typology.  aLinguistic Theories.1 aAlcázar, Asier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCornillie, Bert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoşkun, Hatice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiewald, Gabriele, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDiewald, Gabriele, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGrossman, Francis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaßler, Gerda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHeijnen, Adriënne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKratschmer, Alexandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlungian, Vladimir, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSchenner, Mathias, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aS